org.foxlabs.validation.constraint

Class ConstraintFactory

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.foxlabs.validation.support.AnnotationSupport
      • org.foxlabs.validation.constraint.ConstraintFactory

  • public abstract class ConstraintFactory
extends AnnotationSupport
    Defines a factory that allows to obtain Constraint instances.

    ConstraintFactory is thread-safe.

    Author:
    Fox Mulder
    See Also:
    Constraint

      • createConstraint

        public static <V> Constraint<? super V> createConstraint(Type type,
                                                         Annotation[] annotations,
                                                         String namespace,
                                                         ValidationDefaults defaults)
        Creates a new constraint for the specified generic value type using configuration from the specified annotations.

        This method may return null if there are no constraint annotations specified. Annotations that are not constraint annotations would be skipped.

        Type Parameters:
        V - The value type.
        Parameters:
        type - The type of value to be validated.
        annotations - Array of annotations.
        namespace - Namespace (for example, qualified property name).
        defaults - Validation defaults.
        Returns:
        A new constraint or null if there are no constraint annotations specified.
        Throws:
        ValidationTargetException - if there is an error in constraint declaration.
        See Also:
        createConstraint(Class, Annotation, String, ValidationDefaults)
